#cli #spec
> summarise command — compact graph overview for agent context injection.

eshp summarise [--top N] [--root PATH]

Outputs a warm-start summary of the memory graph:
  - Total size: note count, edge count, unique tag count
  - Top N tags by note count
  - Top N relationship types by edge count
  - Most recently updated notes (by updated_at)
  - Most recently recalled notes (by last_recalled_at — only populated
    when `eshp recall` has been called in this environment)

Designed to be injected into an agent session context at startup so the
agent doesn't start cold. The output is plain text, suitable for piping
into an LLM context window.

last_recalled_at tracking
  Every call to `eshp recall <slug>` updates last_recalled_at in the notes
  table. This is metadata — lives only in .eshp.db (gitignored), never in
  .eshp files. No git conflicts, no accidental commits.

Store methods:
  store.record_recall(slug)     — touch last_recalled_at, auto-commits
  store.summarise(top_n=10)     — returns dict: stats, top_tags, top_rels,
                                  recent_notes, recent_recalls

.implemented-in
-> modules/cli

